questions: Is it something physical/tangible (as opposed to abstract/conceptual)?
Is it a living organism (animal, plant, etc.)?
Was this thing ever definitively alive (not just containing living components)?
Is it something that is currently alive or contains living cells?
Is it a complete/whole organism rather than just a part or product of an organism?
Is it derived from or part of an animal (as opposed to a plant, fungus, or microorganism)?
Is it derived from or part of a plant (as opposed to a fungus or microorganism)?
Is it something commonly consumed by humans as food?
Is it a fruit (botanically defined as containing seeds and developed from a flower)?
Does this fruit grow on trees (as opposed to vines, bushes, or herbaceous plants)?
Is it a citrus fruit (like orange, lemon, grapefruit)?
Is it a stone fruit (containing a single large pit/seed in the center)?
Is it a pome fruit (like apple, pear) with a core containing several seeds?
Is it typically round/spherical in shape (rather than teardrop/elongated)?
Is it predominantly red when ripe (as opposed to green, yellow, or other colors)?
Is an apple what you're thinking of?
